# Schola — Introduction Deck (School X Schola)

**Document type:** Pitch / introduction presentation (13 slides)
**Author / publisher:** Creador Foundation
**Year:** 2024–2025 (copyright © 2024 Creador Foundation; slide 4 also cites © 2025 The Creador Foundation PPAB-01/2017)
**Confidentiality:** Private and Confidential — Do Not Distribute

## Summary

Introductory deck for Schola, a free bilingual (English/Bahasa Malaysia) digital platform targeting Malaysian secondary school students transitioning from school to career. The deck covers mission, rationale, four core features, traction metrics, and a school workshop programme flow.

## Slide-by-Slide Content

### Slide 1 — Cover
Schola is a **FREE digital platform revolutionising career guidance**, guiding students through the school-to-career transition. Powered by Creador Foundation.

### Slide 2 — Mission
> "Helping The Next Generation of Malaysians Discover Their Place in the World!"

### Slide 3 — Approach
Core belief: *"You can't be what you don't know."*
Everyone has talent and potential, but **not everyone has the same access to opportunities**.

### Slide 4 — Why We Created Schola (Research Basis)
From a study with **1,000+ students**:
- **80%** of students have an ambition but **lack essential knowledge** about their chosen careers.
- **70%** do **not actively research** career options.
- Most students only start seriously considering post-SPM pathways **after SPM**.

### Slide 5 — Feature 1: Schola Career Quiz
- Simple and intuitive quiz format → career personality card → customised job matching.
- Developed based on **RIASEC (Holland Codes)**.
- Output: personalised career personality type + list of matched jobs.

### Slide 6 — Feature 2: Subject-to-Job Match
- Students select up to **2 SPM subjects** → platform returns matching careers.
- Exposes students to both familiar and obscure career paths.
- Developed based on results of a student study.

### Slides 7–8 — Feature 3: Job Guides
Six content sections per job:
1. Job description + professional video
2. Salary growth over career stages (from professionals & official sources)
3. Educational pathways to employment
4. Expert advice & tips from professionals
5. Future job opportunity outlook
6. Job knowledge quiz

### Slide 9 — Feature 4: Gaji Goals Game
- Gamified salary simulation: students pick two career paths and compare salary growth over 10 years.
- Shows real-world financial outcomes (e.g., ability to buy a car, travel destinations after 10 years).
- Purpose: help students understand how salaries develop over time to make smarter future decisions.

### Slide 10 — Traction (since 12 August 2024 launch)
- **320,000+** total website users
- **200,000+** of those are students (~63%)

### Slide 11 — School Programme ("Jom Jelajah Masa Depan Bersama Schola")
- **150+ requests** from parents, teachers, and students for school visits.
- Photos show in-classroom and outdoor group activities.

### Slide 12 — Basic Programme Flow (1.5 Hours)
| Duration | Activity |
|---|---|
| 10 min | Schola & FIF Introduction |
| 25 min | Activity 1: Bingo — Kawan Baru, Kerjaya Baru |
| 20 min | Website Exploration |
| 30 min | Activity 2: Reality Check Kerjaya |
| 5 min | Feedback Survey |

Note: Open to incorporating partner activities within the flow.

### Slide 13 — Closing
> "Together, We Guide Students To Better Futures."
